wever, the Principal said, who's going to take care of Madd Washington? I says, I will take care of him. He said, you go home and get a paper from his mother to make sure you're his guardian and I'll let him out. And that was as easy as pi", "doc_title": "60322_John Bubbles oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/60322/"}, {"speaker": "Art Hodes", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "The interviewee discusses a concert produced by 'The Young Women of America' featuring Paul Robeson, and his subsequent refusal to perform there due to Robeson's political associations, but does not indicate a personal relationship with Robeson himself.", "doc_title": "67559_Art Hodes oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/67559/"}]}